node.text:
Time. Feeling. Focus.
.
That was my message to the @alabamafbl team last night but it’s just as important for everyone’s day-to-day life. 
.
If you put in the time, if you truly care, and if you constantly focus, you will achieve success and happiness.

node.text:
13. Wow.
.
That number has meant a lot to me over the years, but today, it’s even more special than ever.
.
I just can’t believe my Ella Bella turns 13 today. My baby girl is officially a teenager!!
.
Ella - everyday you amaze me more than I could have ever imagined. You are smart, mature, talented, caring, and funny. I am so proud of the young woman you are becoming and so lucky and grateful to be your dad. I love you so much. ❤️
.
Happy magical 13th birthday sweetheart! 🎂 🎉 🥳
.
#ellabella #birthdaygirl #teenager #yourdaddyisold

node.text:
I really love this video. I think it displays such a basic, childhood lesson in such a meaningful way … Don’t judge a book by its cover.
.
And that message isn’t limited to someone’s finances. We all have days where things don’t go as planned and you never truly know what a person is going through, or what kind of day they have had ... your first interaction can make all the difference in not only how you see someone, but how they see you. 
.
Be kind. Be open-minded. Be respectful. Make a difference, just by how you treat people.

node.text:
It’s not how you start. It’s how you finish.
.
The magical 2009 @yankees season taught me how true that adage is. I missed the first five weeks of the season recovering from hip surgery. I knew statistically I wasn’t going to post the types of numbers that I had achieved in previous seasons.
.
The important thing is that we were winning and we played great team baseball all year. Heading into the regular season finale, I was 2 HRs & 7 RBI short of continuing my streak of seasons with at least 30 HRs & 100 RBI. I had a chance to tie the great Jimmie Foxx’s all-time record for consecutive 30/100 campaigns, but I was more focused on just staying in the groove for the upcoming playoffs. It seemed out of reach.
.
But my teammates gave me an incredible opportunity in what was my last inning of the regular season & some magic happened. Two players reached base and I connected on a three-run homer. I told teammate Eric Hinske, “If we load the bases and I get up again, hey, you never know.”
.
Amazingly, in the same inning, we kept rallying and had two men on base before the Rays intentionally walked Mark Teixeira. Two pitches later, I put a good swing on a fastball and hit a grand slam. Look at the reaction from the dugout (especially Tex!) I think we were all in disbelief, myself included.
.
The momentum from that game carried me into the best postseason of my career and more importantly, helped bring that 27th world championship to the amazing New York fans.
.
Don’t let an early setback slow you down. Use it to strengthen your focus and do great things!
.
#TBT #2009 #Yanks #worldserieschamps

node.text:
#FlashbackFriday 
.
2009 will always be special to me. It’s the year it all came together for me and my teammates. We were able to make our dreams come true and deliver a championship for the best fans in the world. 
.
After years of struggles in October, I was finally able to put the past behind me and deliver my best postseason. It still feels magical. They say I had a monkey on my back, but to me it felt like King Kong.
.
With each of these swings shown in this video, I felt a sense of relief that I was finally able to help my teammates. I’m still watching these moments with a big grin on my face knowing no one can ever take the championship away from us. 
.
And hey we even made a little extra history with the first ever World Series replay review! Still no bonus points for hitting the camera?! 🤣 
.
Who else is ready for some baseball?! Who do you think wins the World Series this year? #Yankees #Champs #MLB

node.text:
Thank you for taking me into your heart, and on the journey of a lifetime. 

Words can’t do justice to how you make me feel, and what you have meant to my life. Today we celebrate each other. “Just the two of us.” But what I love most is that together, we have truly become one. 

Happy #ValentinesDay, @jlo! I love you. Today and forever. 💕❤️

node.text:
In baseball, the ultimate offensive achievement in one year is called the Triple Crown.
.
For entertainers, I think what @jlo has accomplished in the past 12 months is right up there. 
.
Super Bowl.
NYE.
Inauguration.
.
Amazing. Truly amazing. #Macha ❤️

node.text:
Time. Feeling. Focus.
.
That was my message to the @alabamafbl team last night but it’s just as important for everyone’s day-to-day life. 
.
If you put in the time, if you truly care, and if you constantly focus, you will achieve success and happiness.

node.text:
Two huge milestones, both on Aug. 4, and both lucky enough to be in front of the amazing fans at Yankee Stadium. I’ll never forget homers #500 and #600!
.
#MissItEveryday #Pinstripes #Grateful

node.text:
I’m feeling so grateful today, 

not just for celebrating my big day with my incredible friends and family on this magical trip, but for all of the well-wishes, love and support from everyone. I couldn’t ask for anything more. #ThankYouAll
.
Here’s to a healthy, happy and meaningful 365 days for us all! #46 #AgeIsJustANumber

node.text:
It’s official. Marc Lore and I are so excited to begin a new chapter with the Minnesota Timberwolves and Lynx.
.
Today is a historic day for my family and me. After growing up witnessing my mother work two jobs, I never dreamed this would be possible. My partner Marc grew up in New York working a number of odd jobs and dreaming big, like me.
.
We can’t wait to work together with Glen and Becky Taylor and the ownership group, the Timberwolves organization, and the fans in Minnesota. LET’S GO!

node.text:
On this day five years ago I hit the last HR of my career. At the time, I was confident that I would reach the 700 mark. I never thought that would have been the last time I circled the bases with one swing.
.
Funny how quickly things change. Don’t ever take anything for granted. Stay focused. Stay humbled, through success and adversity.
.
Yes, I did have a chance to go elsewhere and but as I told my girls and family & friends, closing my career as a Yankee with 696 is more valuable to me than hitting No. 700 in any other uniform.
.
And hey, at least my last homer was “An A-bomb from A-Rod” as my good friend and legendary broadcaster John Sterling always said.
.
#yankeeforlife
#loyalty
#thankful

node.text:
Covered all the bases on @BloombergTV yesterday with my friend and business partner, @MarcLore. 
.
When building something special, people make the difference. Our VCP (vision, capital, people) framework and the partnership and capital Marc and I bring creates the perfect foundation for star players to win.
